        "title": "refactor: add embedded run session target seam",
        "body": "## What\n\nAdds a storage-neutral embedded-agent run/session target seam over the existing file-backed implementation. Internal helper runs can now target agent/session identity without requiring callers to construct or pass a `sessionFile` path as normal runtime identity.\n\n## Why\n\nThe SQLite flip needs embedded helper runs, realtime voice consult, and CLI/session-manager boundaries to resolve session targets through the session accessor seam instead of depending on caller-owned file paths.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Adds run session target resolver\n- Migrates embedded helper callers\n- Preserves explicit file-backed compatibility\n- Covers realtime consult session targeting\n\n## Testing\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/run-session-target.test.ts src/context-engine/context-engine.test.ts src/commitments/runtime.test.ts src/crestodian/assistant.test.ts src/hooks/llm-slug-generator.test.ts src/talk/agent-consult-runtime.test.ts src/agents/cli-runner/prepare.test.ts src/agents/cli-runner.before-agent-reply-cron.test.ts`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base clawdbot-d02.1.9.1.24/31b-public-sdk-transcript-target-writer-api --no-web-search --thinking codex=low`\n\nRefs #88838\n",
